  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Magic Chef, value-tier US brand, apartment + ADU + institutional</h2>
    <p>Magic Chef has a long US appliance-brand history across multiple corporate ownership eras; currently CNA International owns Magic Chef with distribution through North American retail channels. The brand's positioning is firmly value-tier, wall oven spec focused on reliable basic function at price-accessible positioning rather than feature depth or aesthetic differentiation. This makes Magic Chef the common specification for LA property-management renovations, multi-unit apartment buildings, ADU and guest-house kitchens, and student housing + senior living + institutional installations where per-unit cost matters more than per-unit feature set.</p>
    <p>Magic Chef's compact 24" wall oven category is particularly relevant to LA's ADU-renovation market, California's permitting changes over the 2010s-2020s have driven a wave of ADU construction, and compact 24" built-in wall ovens fit the space-constrained ADU kitchen layout that 30" standard wall ovens don't accommodate. For LA service, Magic Chef parts distribution runs through the brand's North American channel, common parts 3-5 day lead, some specialty components longer reflecting lower install volume than mainstream brands.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Magic Chef wall oven models we service</h2>
